For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO REMOVE THE LIMITATION OF THE PRACTICE OF
10 NEUROPSYCHOLOGY FROM TECHNICIANS EMPLOYED BY
11 PSYCHOLOGISTS; TO ALLOW PSYCHOLOGY TECHNICIANS TO BE
12 EMPLOYED BY PSYCHOLOGISTS; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
13
14
Subtitle
15
16 TO REMOVE THE LIMITATION OF THE PRACTICE
17 OF NEUROPSYCHOLOGY FROM TECHNICIANS
18 EMPLOYED BY PSYCHOLOGISTS; AND TO ALLOW
19 PSYCHOLOGY TECHNICIANS TO BE EMPLOYED BY
20 PSYCHOLOGISTS.
21
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
23
24 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 17-97-401(a) and (b), concerning
25 technicians employed by psychologists, are amended to read as follows:
26 (a)(1) A technician may be employed by a licensed psychologist in the
27 practice of neuropsychology or a healthcare facility.
28 (2)(A) An individual employed as a technician may be employed
29 only in neuropsychological testing and shall be restricted to the
30 administration and scoring of standardized objective tests shall only
31 practice under the supervision of a licensed psychologist in the following
32 areas:
33 (i) Administration and scoring of standardized
34 objective psychological tests with specific predetermined and manualized
35 procedures;
36 (ii) Manualized cognitive intervention services; and
