4 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 17-97-402(a), concerning additional
5 training for technicians employed by psychologists, is amended to read as
6 follows:
7 (a) The supervising psychologist shall make the technician aware:
8 (1) Of the goals of neuropsychological examination and his or
9 her specific role in achieving those goals;
10 (2) Through additional training, if necessary, of appropriate
11 institutional emergency procedures to deal with various medical emergencies
12 such as heart attack, respiratory arrest, and seizures and of other relevant
13 information; and
14 (3)(2) In addition to medical emergencies, of recommended
15 procedures for dealing with incompetent or adjudicated patients who attempt
16 to leave the testing setting without authorization.
17
18 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 17-97-402(d), concerning additional
19 training of a technician employed by a psychologist, is amended to add an
20 additional subdivision to read as follows:
21 (4) The supervising psychologist shall provide eighty (80) hours
22 of documented training in the following areas:
23 (A) A minimum of four (4) hours of professional ethics,
24 confidentiality, mandatory reporting, best practices in objective test
25 administration, and scoring;
26 (B) A minimum of sixteen (16) hours in the study of test
27 manuals;
28 (C) A minimum of twenty (20) hours of direct observation
29 of test administration and scoring by a licensed psychologist; and
30 (D) A minimum of forty (40) hours of administering and
31 scoring tests under the direct supervision of a licensed psychologist.
32
33 SECTION 4. Arkansas Code § 17-97-402(g)(1), concerning additional
34 training for technicians employed by psychologists, is amended to read as
35 follows:
36 (g)(1) The supervising psychologist shall ensure that each technician
