5 SECTION 5. Arkansas Code § 17-97-403, concerning registration of
6 technicians employed by a licensed psychologist, is amended to add an
7 additional subsection to read as follows:
8 (c) The board may require an annual registration fee of ten dollars
9 ($10.00).
10
11 SECTION 6. Arkansas Code § 17-97-405(a)(1), concerning the supervision
12 of technicians employed by psychologists, is amended to read as follows:
13 (a)(1) An acceptable employment setting for a technician provides
14 shall provide ongoing neuropsychological psychological services or scientific
15 research in a well-defined and established program.
16
17 SECTION 7. Arkansas Code § 17-97-405(c), concerning the supervision of
18 technicians employed by psychologists, is amended to read as follows:
19 (c) The setting shall include a licensed, Arkansas Psychology Board-
20 approved psychologist who is legally and ethically responsible for the
21 oversight of the integrity and quality of the services as well as other
22 resources necessary to meet the employment needs of the technician whose
23 technical assistance is restricted to the practice of neuropsychology
24 psychology and research.
25
26 SECTION 8. Arkansas Code § 17-97-405, concerning the supervision of
27 technicians employed by psychologists, is amended to add an additional
28 subsection to read as follows:
29 (g) A supervising psychologist shall not supervise more than four (4)
30 full-time technicians at one (1) time.
31
32 SECTION 9. Arkansas Code § 17-97-406(a), concerning the qualifications
33 of supervisors for technicians employed by psychologists, is amended to read
34 as follows:
35 (a) A supervising psychologist shall be:
36 (1) Licensed to practice psychology in Arkansas;
4 03-18-2025 14:05:51 JMB032

As Engrossed: H2/19/25 S3/18/25 HB1257
1 (2) Aware of and abide by the ethical principles and state
2 statutes pertaining to the practice of psychology in general and to
3 supervision in particular; and
4 (3) Approved by the Arkansas Psychology Board to practice
5 neuropsychology psychology.
6
7 SECTION 10. Arkansas Code § 17-97-406(d)(1), concerning the
8 qualifications of supervisors for technicians employed by psychologists, is
9 amended to read as follows:
10 (d)(1) A supervising psychologist shall have adequate training,
11 knowledge, and skill to render competently any neuropsychological service
12 which be licensed to practice psychological assessment services in the areas
13 in which the employed technician undertakes.
14
15 SECTION 11. Arkansas Code Title 17, Chapter 97, Subchapter 4, is
16 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
17 17-97-407. Reimbursement — Definition.
18 (a) As used in this section, “health benefit plan” means a plan,
19 policy, contract, certificate, agreement, or other evidence of coverage for
20 healthcare services offered or issued by a healthcare insurer in this state.
21 (b) A psychologist shall be reimbursed for services provided by a
22 technician for the administration and scoring of psychological testing by:
23 (1) The Arkansas Medicaid Program; or
24 (2) A health benefit plan.
